  "response": "In \"The Last Man on Earth,\" the primary story revolves around Phil Miller, who believes he is the last surviving human after a virus wipes out much of the population. The show does not explicitly address the fate of the dead bodies left behind as a result of the pandemic. However, it is implied that the bodies were either left to decay in their locations or that Phil, in his solitary existence, dealt with them in a minimal way. He often expresses a lack of concern for the remnants of society, which underlines the show's themes of isolation and the struggle for survival. The absence of a clear explanation regarding the dead bodies contributes to the show's dark comedy tone and overall atmosphere of a post-apocalyptic world.",
